LOKOJA – The Kogi Central Peoples Democratic Party, (PDP), Senatorial Candidate, Barr. Natasha Hadiza Akpoti-Uduaghan has charged the people of Kogi Central Senatorial District to ensure they register, transfer and collect their Permanent Voters Card , as the situation may demand. Natasha who received the PDP Certificate of Return on Monday in Lokoja alongside other Candidates of the party in the state, further urged the people to turn out en-masse and vote her and her PDP teammates in order to ensure reformation from local communities to the Sate and the country at large. “There’s an awakening of the youths across the country in the pursuit of good governance through credible leadership and Kogi Central isn’t left behind this movement. Joining my fellow candidates of our great party the PDP to receive the Certificate of Return births a new phase in our electoral process towards emerging victorious at the 2023 polls by God’s grace. “To this end, I implore the people people of Kogi central, state and country to earnestly participate in all legal processes as stipulated by the electoral bodies from registration, transfer and collection of PVCs to turning en-masse on the election day to vote Natasha Akpoti-Uduaghan and her teammates in the PDP so together we shall reform our communities, districts, state and country for better Social Justice and Economic Development.”